oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Street flooded in Columbia
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a group of unidentified people standing on the side of a road looking out towards the street that is flooded in front of them. Several cars, including a truck, appear to be stopped on or near the floodwater. Note: this image appears on two separate negatives.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Streets; People; Floods; Automobiles
